    "cv": "Markus Pantsar is a guest professor at the chair of Prof. Dr. Gabriele Gramelsberger (Theory of Science and Technology). He specializes on philosophy of mathematics, philosophy of artificial intelligence, logic, epistemology, philosophy of mind, and philosophy of science. Pantsar is the author of the book Numerical Cognition and the Epistemology of Arithmetic (Cambridge University Press, 2024). He has published more than 30 articles in important international journals, including Synthese, Erkenntnis, Minds and Machines, AI & Society, Ethics and AI, Philosophia Mathematica, Topoi, Theoria and Frontiers in Psychology. After getting his PhD in 2009 at the University of Helsinki, he worked in several projects there between 2010 and 2021. Since 2017, he also holds the Title of Docent in theoretical philosophy at the University of Helsinki. Between 2013 and 2014, he was a Visiting Researcher at the Munich Center for Mathematical Philosophy, Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München, Germany. From 2021 to 2022 he was a Senior Fellow at the Käte Hamburger Kolleg Aachen: Cultures of Research. Having started at the Chair of Theory of Science and Technology in October 2022, Pantsar teaches the lecture courses \\“Introduction to Philosophy of Science and Technology\\” and \\“Philosophy of the Computational Sciences\\” in addition to the seminars \\“Theories of Research\\”, \\“Modelling for Policy\\”, \\“Philosophy of Mind\\” and \\“Introduction to Pragmatist Philosophy\\”. He also co-runs the Master Seminar in the Governance of Technology and Innovation (GovTec) program with Professor Stefan Böschen.",
